<p>F 30 Sun<br/>Tam &amp; I go to [Pewsey?].<br/>Tam's chain breaks &amp; we tow one another Home. 12 miles in 1 &frac34; hours. Get home in a filthy state &amp; drinks are my only consolation<br/>Wrote Dad. P.C.  &amp; Mum 10 page letter.</p>
<p>F 1 July Mon<br/>We have Magic Lantern Show &amp; I play the Piano. Generally mess around &amp;  tidy up</p>
<p>Dream all night that I've got 42</p>
<p>F 2 Tues.<br/>Recd letter from Doris. B.2's play Bulford &amp; win through on Bad Playing. Chain up bike. We have jellies etc. I first try the [sharing?] water pocket and it is O.K. May comes back from Port Hole strike.<br/>Wrote Mrs Williams. Nancy Dewan. Roy.</p>
<p>F 3 Wed<br/>Glorious Day T &amp; I ride to S'hampton.<br/>It is lovely. We have fruit salads [indecipherable] Wharf where we first landed from Egypt. Visit Shirley. Redbridge [indecipherable] Romsey. Ride 22 miles through lovely Hampshire in under 2 hours. Call at Mrs Edmonds. See Roy's Name in latrine at Romsey</p>
<p>F 4 Th<br/>Very hot day. Half Holiday. [indecipherable] out to play cricket. Pellen gets 74 &amp;  all 170. [indecipherable]<br/>Go out 29 out for Tennis &amp; cricket &amp; Play catches with Wright  &amp;  Top.<br/>Recd 6 letters from Home. Maisie C, Marie Auntie Annie. Marg White. Mrs White. Bess. Lottie. Bert<br/>Meet George Wilson from B'wood playing cricket.<br/>Wrote Jennie &amp; Maisie</p>
<p>F 5 Fri<br/>Very Hot. Try to fit [indecipherable]   &amp;  make "into small of the 1 &frac12; hrs work. Lean a lot [indecipherable] bike &amp; generally tidy up more office to Expense Store.</p>
<p>F 6 Sat<br/>Go to S'hampton &amp;  ride across Punt (Floating Bridge) to [Burlenden??] Bridge  &amp;  Park Gate. Back &amp; sit on Pier. It is lovely &amp; we think of sitting on our own Pier. Have supper with Mrs Edmonds &amp; arrive Home about 11.30 pm.<br/>Have a glorious day but [indecipherable] opened 11/-on tricker fell hungry all the time</p>
